The paper focuses on mean-field-type game theory and its application in engineering practice, which suggests that it belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also introduces psychological patterns to better capture and understand behaviors, which indicates that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper conducts an experiment with human participants, which suggests that it could also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
